Name: purulent acute otitis media
Definition: A suppurative otitis media with sudden onset and a short course.

Name: obsolete metastasis to lymph node
Definition: A suppurative otitis media with sudden onset and a short course.

Name: chronic purulent otitis media
Definition: A suppurative otitis media which is persistent and long-lasting.

Name: chronic tubotympanic suppurative otitis media
Definition: A suppurative otitis media which is an inflammatory disease of the middle ear cleft characterized by the presence of a persisting perforation within the pars tensa of the tympanic membrane
Synonym: intestinal infection due to enterotoxigenic E. coli
